# ==============================================================================
# EDULOCKA SMART CONTRACTS — ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# ==============================================================================
#
# HOW TO USE THIS FILE:
#   1. Copy this file and rename the copy to ".env"
#      Command: cp .env.example .env
#   2. Fill in your actual values in the .env file
#   3. NEVER commit your .env file to GitHub!
#      (it's already in .gitignore to protect you)
#
# WHY DO WE USE .ENV FILES?
# Environment variables store secrets (private keys, API keys) separately
# from your code. This way, if you share your code on GitHub, your secrets
# stay private and safe.
# ==============================================================================


# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PRIVATE KEY — Your wallet's secret key for signing transactions
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# WHAT IS A PRIVATE KEY?
# Every blockchain wallet has two keys:
#   - Public Key (your "address"): Like your email address — you can share it
#   - Private Key: Like your password — NEVER share it with anyone!
#
# The private key lets you sign transactions (prove it's really you).
# Anyone with your private key can steal all your funds!
#
# HOW TO GET YOUR PRIVATE KEY FROM METAMASK:
#   1. Open MetaMask browser extension
#   2. Click the three dots (⋯) next to your account name
#   3. Click "Account Details"
#   4. Click "Show Private Key"
#   5. Enter your MetaMask password
#   6. Copy the key (starts with a long hex string)
#
# ⚠️  CRITICAL SAFETY RULES:
#   - ONLY use a TEST wallet (create a new one just for development)
#   - NEVER use a wallet that holds real cryptocurrency
#   - NEVER share your private key with anyone
#   - NEVER commit this .env file to GitHub
#
PRIVATE_KEY=your_private_key_here


# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SEPOLIA RPC URL — Connection to the Sepolia test network
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# WHAT IS AN RPC URL?
# RPC stands for "Remote Procedure Call". Think of it as a phone number
# that lets your code call the Ethereum network and say:
#   "Hey, deploy this contract" or "Hey, read this data"
#
# You need a service provider to get an RPC URL. Free options:
#
# OPTION 1: Alchemy (recommended for beginners)
#   1. Go to https://www.alchemy.com
#   2. Create a free account
#   3. Create a new app → select "Ethereum" → "Sepolia"
#   4. Copy the HTTPS URL from your app dashboard
#
# OPTION 2: Infura
#   1. Go to https://infura.io
#   2. Create a free account
#   3. Create a new project → select "Ethereum"
#   4. Copy the Sepolia endpoint URL
#
SEPOLIA_RPC_URL=https://eth-sepolia.g.alchemy.com/v2/YOUR-API-KEY


# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ETHERSCAN API KEY — For verifying your contract's source code
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# WHAT IS ETHERSCAN?
# Etherscan (https://etherscan.io) is like a search engine for the blockchain.
# You can look up transactions, wallet balances, and smart contracts.
#
# WHY VERIFY ON ETHERSCAN?
# When you deploy a contract, Etherscan only shows unreadable bytecode.
# Verifying uploads your source code so anyone can read it — this builds trust.
#
# HOW TO GET AN API KEY:
#   1. Go to https://etherscan.io
#   2. Create a free account
#   3. Go to https://etherscan.io/myapikey
#   4. Click "Add" to create a new API key
#   5. Copy the key and paste it below
#
ETHERSCAN_API_KEY=your_etherscan_api_key_here
